column5: Crossed into Ft. Frances today. Got into a short line at 1:05pm, finally got up to the agent at 2:15pm. Spent 5 minutes with the agent, showed him our passports, vac card, and test results. More questions than usual, but now we’re headed fishing!
Our border crossing last week was the same. We drove right up to the border agent and it took 5-7 minutes. Very easy.
My border crossing was more of the same. Only reason it took a little longer is because I shot the **** with the border guard and had a firearm to check in.
Each of us also had the ID Now test thru Walgreens.

Paid toll at 3:13, was at the agent at 4:13. Looked at passports and COVID test paperwork the most. Asked the usual questions plus current health conditions. We were done in 5 minutes.Used the Walgreens ID NOW test.

Crossed at Pigeon River at 0200, only one there and in 5 minutes we were on our way. In Ignace now waiting for Vern’s bait shop to open and then off to Savant. Great to be back as it rained the whole drive since we cleared the border
